&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   25 lives-eq/$1k · 16% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up GiveWell top charity (AMF) · 55%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + resilience_undermines_deterrence + time_of_perils_exit + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy1WW1v2sgW%2FitH0d17IQvE5jWQm5XShOxWN22jJNVq1VR0sAeYje3xnbFDaLf97feZMQaTmBsktF8qYo%2FPec5z3qffDnw%2BYWmQnEufHwwOjo7o9PSU7hQTESWSPMW%2BLvBjHtF92nTcNs2lCvxHwec0d0edUXfkuiO3PXLxo0cVnciY3F7VSLmPIO1M6zSMEyEj8mYQOiCHYqakNxMsMDLdfpNcmjA1YnO2GM3SkEU6f9GhSZqkii8fj0KWJFyN5iKZjXyhPZlGiYim%2BfEuRbL4fLTx9UqbS4prEQgeeXyURj5XoYi4HvkcwpV5ujrapkSEfCQno5grEegRfxLJ6m2XAvFo9IhopEWYBswamr%2FuET7SMhqxyYR7FpAhzvIyZN6M2JocoYnR9SKZ4fdEBJzA%2F%2Fq1PqJkxhJivq9rQA%2BnGcQklRWmeB2cstDgFxrPkxnP6P6XBoORZ2WckCfDWGpD2OoAvjUEcB%2BPhLbSdMIinwUy4hQiKoIGfVk5ffj4xUA1n%2FOnGEbhw0cWpJzkxEpYx0fDCnvDdULjdEGWZ%2FOh5kXDBnT2ljSb8GRBlRvuz6X06QaHmPJm1UzGr8P3w5uzu%2BEFjRc05RFXLOGNeJGHJPfhkyJZh3hZQywkGSTDJyRZWR%2FhXZUYw0OpEIEr3nR2NiOFxTHCQzfodhE2AjmNpApZUPkWd2oU9zvfq1aW9Vnf%2BYnO357