17]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   2.3 lives-eq/$1k · 6% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up GiveWell top charity (AMF) · 63%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + resilience_undermines_deterrence + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWGtz2kgW%2FSu3XDu74AEs8TR4PVVOjGdS62RctlNTU3GKNFIDvZHU2m7JmGSS376nWxIIW2yo5YsLS61zz33f21%2BPfD5jaZC8lj4%2FGh2dnND5%2BTndKyYiSiR5in1Z4ccyooe07bhdWkoV%2BI%2BCL2npTnqT%2FsR1Jy7%2BDqimExmTO6gbiIcIUBdap2GcCBmRtwDiiByKmZLeQrDAALrDNrk0Y2rClmw1WaQhi3TxokezNEkVzx9PQpYkXE2WIllMfKE9mUaJiObF8T5Fsvx8svX1WppLimsRCB55fJJGPlehiLie%2BBzgyjxdH%2B1TIB4NkogmWoRpwKwqxesBxVxpGU3YbMY9K9LYxWo%2BZt6C2EZ9oYnRzSpZ4PdMBJxg3s1rfULJgiXEfF83wA8%2BMZxIKgumeBNWY6FhKDSeJwueGfQfGjaKPItxRp4MY6mNSdYH8K1Rkft4JLRF0wmLfBbIiFMIpwct%2BrT26fjxk6FqPudPMZTCh48sSDnJmUXYuL9lwV5xndA0XZG1pPlQ87JiI7p4Q5rNeLKi2i33l1L6dItDTHmLeobx6%2Fjd%2BPbifnxJ0xXNecQVS3grXhURx32RbBnrGC8b8HaSUTL2BJLFeg%2F%2FqcQoHkqFGFvbTWdnM6OwOEYA6BbdrcJWIOeRVCELal%2FjXoPiYe9b3WJZnw2dn%2Bj1mzN7csoTlj2NlZyyKaIoAZGpNMr7Jl0%2BOA1yP7boinmJhEymeAaFA7HxRJQ